00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,839
Yes, YOU.

2
00:00:01,789 --> 00:00:05,223
The person watching at two times speed.

3
00:00:05,223 --> 00:00:07,894
Slow down for this part.

4
00:00:07,894 --> 00:00:21,289
But here's where it gets really interesting,  - Debezium is the most common source connector — it uses CDC (Change Data Capture) to stream DB changes via the binlog/WAL.

5
00:00:21,289 --> 00:00:30,355
Schema Registry uses a binary wire format: 1 magic byte + 4-byte schema ID + Avro payload.

6
00:00:30,355 --> 00:00:37,065
BACKWARD compatibility is the Confluent default and the safest for most teams.

7
00:00:37,065 --> 00:00:46,118
Plot twist: ChatGPT uses the exact same concepts we're learning here to handle millions of concurrent users.

